Sizes of different primitive data types in JAVA:
	-				1byte	-->	8bits		-->	[-2^7, 2^7 -1]
	-1short		-->	2bytes	-->	16bits		-->	[-2^15, 2^15 -1]
	-1int		-->	4bytes	-->	32bits		-->	[-2^31, 2^31 -1]
	-1long		-->	8bytes	-->	64bits		-->	[-2^31, 2^31 -1]
	

	-1float		-->	4bytes	-->	32bits		-->	[-2^31, 2^31 -1]
	-1double	-->	8bytes	-->	64bits		-->	[-2^63, 2^63 -1]
	
	
	-1boolean	-->	------	-->	1bit		-->	{1}

	
	-1char		-->	2bytes	-->	16bits		-->	[-2^15, 2^15 -1]